Apps":false},{"$kind":"Shelf","impressionMetrics":{"fields":{"id":"23","name":"","impressionType":"ratingsDetails","idType":"sequential","impressionIndex":2}},"contentType":"reviews","marker":null,"items":[{"$kind":"Review","id":"10632466943","title":"Awesome","date":"2023-11-27T21:03:03.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Hands down the best matrix client for iOS / iPadOS. The only problem I’ve seen is jumping doesn’t seem to work correctly for me. When it tries to jump to the last read message then it winds up at the bottom again. Otherwise an absolutely awesome client. Great if you’re using heisenbridge for irc.","rating":4,"reviewerName":"GGonJR","dateAuthorText":"* null * · GGonJR"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"11135069849","title":"Unreliable, glitchy, crashes since latest update","date":"2024-04-08T12:01:38.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"I wasn't a huge fan of this app, I've yet to find a way to  attach videos that doesn't require saving them as files first. On top of that there is a bug that shows notifications until you come out of the chat and go back in which is really annoying. \n\nSince the latest update though, things have gotten much worse. The app has become extremely slow, I get error messages multiple times per day and the entire app then crashes. Now I am hearing notifications and I know I have messages, but they don't load unless I quit the app and reload, which lately takes forever. \n\nReporting bugs or submitting crash reports requires you to sign into git hub. I'm not going to do that.","rating":1,"reviewerName":"Aeonix99","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Aeonix99"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"10188932876","title":"Worse UI of my life","date":"2023-07-27T19:30:56.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Is there supposed to be a discover tab somewhere? I don't have any way to search for a room when I have an identifier. The search tab I paste the identifier into has some option to change the server but it only appears after pasting the identifier - what's the point of a well defined identifier if the software doesn't bother to parse it ? Clearly I don't know how to use matrix but this app just makes me feel like an idiot for not being able to join a server and room I have the name of.\n\nThe \"help\" tab just goes to their git issue tracker, nothing in the form of a user guide I could search for a step by step \"how to\" of the basics.","rating":1,"reviewerName":"lookalivesoftware","dateAuthorText":"* null * · lookalivesoftware"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"7669356585","title":"By far the best Matrix app - Bar a few key features","date":"2021-08-08T14:21:42.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"FluffyChat is one of the BEST matrix apps I have had the pleasure of using. The only features I would like are \n1. Joining a space joins all the rooms in that space automatically. Its a bit tedious to join the rooms manually.\nAnd \n2. Swiping down on the keyboard hides it. \nOther than these two minor complaints this app is AMAZING. I love it. God speed to the dev team!","rating":5,"reviewerName":"010100110110000101101101","dateAuthorText":"* null * · 010100110110000101101101"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"13391113171","title":"Copy Paste image functionality?","date":"2025-11-13T03:13:18.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"I have seen many updates in this app, yet none of them include a paste feature which includes images yet. Can we get that pleaseeee? Keeping photos on my phone loads up a lot of storage over time, which can be cut down with this feature. This other feature is pushing it, but can the app also have more customization? I prefer this app over other element clients for its colors and stickers functionality, but the colors are getting dull…","rating":2,"reviewerName":"nfvbxfff","dateAuthorText":"* null * · nfvbxfff"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"9292614921","title":"One of the best matrix clients","date":"2022-11-15T17:01:41.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"I would like to see better copy / paste and ability to send files to a room using the share menu. Very fast and works well on iPad too.","rating":5,"reviewerName":"Kirkland248","dateAuthorText":"* null * · Kirkland248"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"10413496800","title":"It was great…","date":"2023-09-27T18:56:13.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Until I turned on the lock app option so I would have to enter a passcode to get in. I know what you’re thinking. I forgot the passcode, but no. Every time I try to open the app now it just stays as a blank white screen and that’s it. I can’t even use the app. I’ve tried reinstalling it multiple times, and it just doesn’t seem to fix the problem.","rating":2,"reviewerName":"hwjkdvfjlapwnevakaiwoksj","dateAuthorText":"* null * · hwjkdvfjlapwnevakaiwoksj"},{"$kind":"Review","id":"10065400017","title":"Phantom notifications","date":"2023-06-23T21:23:31.000Z","dateText":"* null *","contents":"Always says I have notifications but when I open the app everything is showing I’ve read it. This happens on both my phone and iPad. Absolutely kills me and wastes a lot of time opening the app thinking someone has reached out. Husband and I will be looking into other methods to message.","rating":2,"reviewerName":"perry.pe","dateAuthorText":"* null * · perry.pe"}],"url":null,"mergeWhenFetched":false,"fetchStrategy":"onPageLoad","batchGroup":null,"seeAllAction":null,"footerTitle":null,"footerAction":null,"eyebrow":null,"eyebrowArtwork":null,"footerStyle":null,"titleArtwork":null,"subtitle":null,"isHorizontal":false,"isHidden":false,"rowsPerColumn":null,"background":{"type":"none"},"contentsMetadata":{"type":"none"},"isPersonalized":false,"shouldFilterApps":false,"id":"ReviewsPage.ShelfId.helpful","presentationHints":{"isSortable":true,"isSeeAllContext":true}}],"title":null,"presentationOptions":[],"isIncomplete":false,"pageMetrics":{"$kind":"PageMetrics","instructions":[],"custom":{}},"$kind":"ReviewsPage","trailingNavBarAction":null,"adamId":"1551469600","nextPage":{"url":"x-as3-i